quran[33]{c,v,t}:
  68,1,Nun. By the pen and that which they inscribe
  68,2,"thou art not, by the blessing of thy Lord, possessed"
  68,3,Truly thine shall be a reward unceasing
  68,4,And truly thou art of an exalted character
  68,5,So thou wilt see and they will see
  68,6,which of you is afflicted
  68,7,"Truly thy Lord knows best those who stray from His way, and He knows best those who are rightly guided"
  68,8,so obey not the deniers
  68,9,They wish that thou might compromise and that they might compromise
  68,10,So obey not any vile oath-monger—
  68,11,slanderer spreading calumny
  68,12,"hinderer of good, a transgressing sinner"
  68,13,"churlish, surly, and ignoble withal—"
  68,14,simply because he possesses wealth and children
  68,15,"When Our signs are recited unto him he says, “Fables of those of old.”"
  68,16,We shall brand him on the snout
  68,17,"Truly We tried them, just as We tried the owners of the garden who vowed that they would harvest its fruit in the morning"
  68,18,And they made no exception
  68,19,Whereupon a visitation from your Lord came upon it while they slept
  68,20,such that it became like a garden plucked
  68,21,Then they called to one another in the morning
  68,22,“Go early to your tillage if you would harvest.”
  68,23,So they set forth while whispering to one another
  68,24,“Surely no indigent shall come to you therein today.”
  68,25,"And they set out early, strong in their purpose"
  68,26,"Then when they saw it, they said, “Surely, we are astray"
  68,27,Nay! we are deprived!”
  68,28,"The most moderate of them said, “Did I not say to you, why do you not glorify?”"
  68,29,"They said, “Glory be to our Lord! Truly we were wrongdoers.”"
  68,30,"Then they turned to one another, reproaching each other"
  68,31,"saying, “Oh, woe unto us! Truly we were rebellious"
  68,32,Perhaps our Lord will give us something better in its stead. Truly we beseech our Lord.”
  68,33,"Such is the punishment; yet the punishment of the Hereafter is surely greater, if they but knew"